<font color="#FF0000">I READ NOTHING OF VALUE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 22:34:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
It is impossible to write well on the<br>
operations of war, if a man has no <br>
experience on active service, as it is <br>
to write well on politics without having <br>
been engaged in political transactions and<br>
vicissitudes.<br><br>
Polybius, 200-118 B.C.<br><br>
It is painful for the disillusioned to have the heart<br>
of a sheep and the tongue of an adder.  Listen <br>
not to their words for there is little of value.<br><br>
When the enemy is at ease, be able to<br>
weary him; when well fed, to starve him;<br>
when at rest, to make him move.<br><br>
I have often thought that the fierce hostility<br>
is a manifestation of the sleep we make them lose.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


